# .clinerules
#
# Project-wide linting and performance rules.
# These rules are inspired by the steering guidelines in `steering/feat.md` and
# aim to improve execution speed, maintainability, and code consistency.
#
# Usage:
#   The custom CLI tool `cliner` (or any compatible linter) can read this file
#   to enforce the following checks.
#
# Rules:
#   async_await: true                # Enforce use of async/await for async operations
#   no_console: true                # Disallow console.log/debug in production code
#   max_loop_complexity: 1          # Encourage O(N) loops; avoid nested loops where possible
#   prefer_array_methods: true      # Prefer map/filter/reduce over manual for loops
#   snake_case_db_fields: true      # Ensure DB field names use snake_case (e.g., user_id)
#   dto_validation: true            # Require DTO validation for all incoming requests
#   naming:
#     classes: PascalCase
#     functions: camelCase
#     variables: camelCase
#     constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
#   typescript_strict: true         # Enable strict mode checks
#   import_sort: true               # Sort imports alphabetically
#   no_unused_imports: true         # Remove unused imports
#
# These rules help keep the codebase fast, clean, and aligned with the domain‑driven
# design principles outlined in the steering documents.